<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="57889" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57889">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57889">
Palearctic species (
<bibRefCitation author="Majka, Christopher G." journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="57889" pagination="48 - 72" refId="B6008427" refString="Majka, Christopher G., Klimaszewski, Jan, 2012. Introduced Staphylinidae (Coleoptera) in the Maritime Provinces of Canada. The Canadian Entomologist 140 (1): 48 - 72" title="Introduced Staphylinidae (Coleoptera) in the Maritime Provinces of Canada" volume="140" year="2012">Majka and Klimaszewski 2012</bibRefCitation>
): Central-southern Europe, Russia (European, Siberia, Far East), Ukraine, Armenia, Georgia, Turkey, Azerbaijan, Israel, Iran, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Korea, Japan and Nepal; introduced into Canada (
<bibRefCitation author="Isaia, Marco" journalOrPublisher="Arachnologische Mitteilungen" pageId="0" pageNumber="57889" refId="B6008440" refString="2000 ITIS Species The Catalogue of Life https://www.catalogueoflife.org/ 2020-03-03T00:00:00+02:00" year="2018">ITIS Species 2000 2020</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pace, R." journalOrPublisher="Consorzio Parco Lombardo della Valle del Ticino, Servizio Agricoltura" pageId="0" pageNumber="57889" pagination="263 - 281" refId="B6300111" refString="Pace, R., 2005. Note su alcune Aleocharinae dell'area euro-mediterranea con particolare riguardo ataxa di Piemonte, Sardegna e Grecia (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). In: Rivista Piemontesedi Storia Naturale.: 263 - 281" title="Note su alcune Aleocharinae dell'area euro-mediterranea con particolare riguardo ataxa di Piemonte, Sardegna e Grecia (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae)." volumeTitle="Rivista Piemontesedi Storia Naturale." year="2005">Pace 2005</bibRefCitation>
). In Italy, the species is currently known only for the peninsula (
<bibRefCitation author="Ruffo, S." journalOrPublisher="Memorie del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 2. serie, Sezione Scienze della Vita 16" pageId="0" pageNumber="57889" refId="B6300128" refString="Ruffo, S., Stoch, F., 2005. Checklist e distribuzione della fauna italiana. Memorie del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 2.serie, Sezione Scienze della Vita 16" title="Checklist e distribuzione della fauna italiana" year="2005">Ruffo and Stoch 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="57889" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57889">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57889">
Found in open areas under vegetation, stone, mosses and decomposing materials. A very eurytopic species adapted to a wide range of ground conditions: it can be found on dry, heathy and sandy soils; on damp loam and in humic soils; in wet soil and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Bryopsida" family="Sphagnaceae" genus="Sphagnum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sphagnum" order="Sphagnales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57889" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57889">Sphagnum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Often found in proximity of ants (
<bibRefCitation author="Majka, Christopher G." journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="57889" pagination="48 - 72" refId="B6008427" refString="Majka, Christopher G., Klimaszewski, Jan, 2012. Introduced Staphylinidae (Coleoptera) in the Maritime Provinces of Canada. The Canadian Entomologist 140 (1): 48 - 72" title="Introduced Staphylinidae (Coleoptera) in the Maritime Provinces of Canada" volume="140" year="2012">Majka and Klimaszewski 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
